# Coinbase Design System

The Coinbase Design System (CDS) is a component library built with TypeScript. It uses React for web components and React Native for mobile components. CDS provides a set of consistent, reusable UI components that follow Coinbase's design principles and guidelines across web and mobile applications.

## Core Packages

The design system is organized into several core packages in the monorepo:

- Web components: import from `@cbhq/cds-web2` found at [package.json](mdc:packages/cds-web2/package.json)
- Mobile components: import from `@cbhq/cds-mobile2` found at [package.json](mdc:packages/cds-mobile2/package.json)
- Shared utilities: import from `@cbhq/cds-common2` found at [package.json](mdc:packages/cds-common2/package.json)
- Illustrations: import from `@cbhq/illustrations` found at [package.json](mdc:packages/illustrations/package.json)
